LESLIE CHOW brushed the gate on the start, pulled the rider between horses improving position down the backside, hounded the pace three deep at the half, dueled for the lead outside throughout the far turn, could not keep up to the winner turning for home and crossed the line besting the rest easily for second place. ANSELMO tracked the front trio four deep outside in a stacked up field at the half, started to make a move four wide around runners three furlongs out, could not find another gear to threaten the first two in upper stretch but did fight on to the wire, winning the battle for show at the finish. MIDWAY MISCHIEF was reined back when in tight soon after the break to trail inside early on, kept a close eye on the contesting threesome at the half running between horses in the two path, was roused three wide on the turn making little impact and fought determinedly down the stretch on the fence settling for a minor role but just missed in the end for third money. BET N WIN tracked the front pair just outside on the first turn, watched the trio engage up front at the half between runners in the three path, rallied three wide putting in a mild run at the three furlong marker until the quarter pole and faded between in the final eighth of a mile. DREAMS AND SCHEMES prompted the pace between down the back straight, could not maintain forward position into the turn, was checked mildly three eighths from the wire and could not regroup down the stretch to be involved at the finish. SIR SAMUEL was bumped inside on the break, tucked inside on the rail watching the front duo through the first turn, shuffled back on the fence to trail at the half but still quite in range, was urged on the rail three furlongs out, made little headway around the far turn and was not a factor running down the lane inside.

BRAQUET was three deep in the second flight watching the foursome early on, made an early move getting better position three wide outside keeping tabs on the contesting duo on the turn, was asked left handed for more run at the quarter pole to be in the hunt four wide straightening out for home and stubbornly fought between foes late to be a solid third at the finish. RED SAMURAI prompted outside four deep in the early going, hounded the frontrunner outside running around the bend, was in the hunt in the three path turning for home, chased the winner in vain until the seventy yard marker and tired nearing the wire losing positions late. MAJESTIC APPEAL pressed the issue in the two path down the backside, was coaxed to maintain position at the half, could not quicken on the fence with others in midturn and faded in the final sixteenth. VRANA (IRE) settled in mid-pack inside down the backstretch, checked briefly when in tight at the half mile marker, could see the field running through the turn and was never involved driving to the finish line. AMONG THE ROSES dueled three wide between rivals for the lead in the early going, came under a ride with horses on each side tracking the front pair, three furlongs from the line, could not keep pace by the quarter pole and faltered in upper stretch.

ANGELOU took control inside from the start, set a modest pace while hounded outside down the backstretch, continued stubbornly up front setting the fractions on the final turn, repelled the first challenger outside in upper stretch, found more when asked right handed in mid-stretch to keep the inside rival at bay but gave way to a strong closing winner near the wire in an extra game front running performance. IL MALOCCHIO was brushed outside to begin, tucked in nicely on the rail behind the front duo on the first turn, rated kindly down the backstretch nestled behind the leaders, took closer order on the fence around the final bend, loomed on the rail at the top of the lane, was battling inside, inching closer coming to the wire but needed more late to pose a threat. MOUFFY was brushed inside at the start, was under a snug hold in the two path behind the front pair in the first turn, tracked the top two running between horses down the backstretch, rallied three wide at the quarter posing a threat by the time they hit the lane, was repelled by the frontrunner in upper stretch, continued to stubbornly finish up to the wire but settled for a minor role when crossing the line. EPHRATA (GB) stalked near the rear inside on the first turn, settled in a rhythm in mid-pack inside down the backstretch, coaxed for run on the rail three eighth from the line, shifted outside four wide for the stretch drive and ran on mildly to the finish line. SARATOGA VISION was pushed in on the break, co-trailed on the outside down the back straight, made little headway on the far turn and ran on willingly passing runners down the stretch. DEVIL'S BIT tracked outside four wide in the beginning, settled four deep in midfield down the backside, was roused three wide three furlongs to go putting in a brief run outside runners, had a chance for a small share in the five path at the top of the lane, could not sustain the run and was one paced to the wire. WHIMSICAL DANCE was checked mildly at the start, co-trailed on the inside down the backstretch, kept pace with rivals while saving ground on the fence in the final turn but could not offer a finish on the rail driving to the line. SOUPER HOITY TOITY tracked the front pair three wide into the first turn, continued to have a good position outside watching the front two down the backside, was asked for to go three wide outside runners three eighths from home, could not find more on the far turn and yielded between foes at the quarter pole. TAMARAMA (GB) pressed the pace outside on the first turn, was content to sit just outside the pacesetter down the backstretch, was hard ridden between horses but could not match strides with foes starting a run in midturn and backed through the field at the quarter pole.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPUN GLASS was outpaced in the early going racing last but one, angled in leaving the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, encouraged along by the top of the stretch while guided out, split rivals four deep coming past the sixteenth pole taking the lead and holding sway. AWESOME TREAT broke just a tad awkwardly but was none the worse, settled off the pace two to three wide into the turn, moved out five wide coming into upper stretch and loomed a threat, was outkicked by the winner but secured the place. LOYALTY pressed then prompted the pace from outside two to three wide, took the lead about the five-sixteenths, moved clear into upper stretch, was otukicked. HAZELBROOK pursued from between runners on the second flight moving out from three to four wide past the quarter pole, loomed a threat in upper stretch but could only run on evenly late. SOUPER MUNNINGS broke a step slowly, lacked early speed bringing up the rear along the inside, came out for the stretch run, kicked on well but too late. READY TO VENTURE (GB) was outsprinted in a scramble for the early lead then content to track in behind racing inside foes but just off the rail, kept on evenly in the stretch. OUR FLASH DRIVE was well-placed stalking a lively pace four to five wide, moved out six to seven deep for the stretch run, lacked the needed late kick. ARTIE'S PRINCESS raced outside off the pace five to six wide on the turn, swung out a bit further for the drive, failed to rally. HARD EDGE was stoutly urged from the start, set a pressured pace inside, weakened in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRIZZEL TRAZZEL was bumped on the break, was patiently allowed to find her stride trailing down the back straight, began to mount a rally three wide picking up runners midway on the turn, swung out in the seven path full of run turning for home, took command at the sixteenth pole and was drawing away smartly when crossing the finish. HOT OMELET stalked near the rear in the beginning, advanced smartly down the backside, had to be throttled down behind runners seven sixteenths from home, waited behind a wall of runners through the turn, finally had a clear path four wide at the furlong marker, quickly burst between runners and closed strongly late to get second. ITS A BIRDIE settled between horses in the mid-pack in the beginning, improved along the backside, was scrubbed on gaining on the leaders running around the turn, was in the hunt in the four path driving to the finish, briefly had the lead at the furlong marker but could not hold off the closers late and faded to just miss holding for second at the wire. SPEEDY JOHNY trailed the field at the half, rallied three wide, following the path set by the winner throughout the turn, swung outside seven wide with run and closed in well under left handed urging to get up for a minor share in the end. ONANDONANDON stalked in the third flight four deep on the outside at the half, was hard ridden to keep position four wide with runners on either side midpoint on the turn, raced in the five path to be in the mix at the top of the lane, contended for a share between foes at the sixteenth pole and tired in deep stretch. ROOKIE COURT prompted the pace outside three deep down the backside, chased the frontrunner outside foes throughout the turn and faded inside with a sixteenth to run. GOLD FORESTER tracked the front trio between horse in the three path down the back straight, roused between rivals three wide midway around the bend, was in tight in the four path straightening out for the drive and finished up mildly to the wire. TAYLORMOON travelled outside runners four deep at the half in mid-pack, offered a brief run five wide around horses three furlongs out, was in range six wide driving to the finish and weakened in mid-stretch. GOLDEN TRAIN pressed the pace inside down the backstretch, chased the pacesetter on the rail through the turn and gave wat three wide at the furlong marker. TENPENNY NAIL stalked on the rail near the rear in the early stages, made no headway on the rail around the bend, lost her path on the fence at the eighth pole, angled outside late and could not offer a finish in deep stretch. SWEET NOLA travelled in midfield inside at the half, saved ground keeping pace throughout the turn, shifted inwards to the rail at the furlong marker, was steadied at the sixteenth pole and could not be a factor after that. VERI UNIFIED had a slim lead with runners on either side in the early going, opened up on the chasing rivals through the turn, was clinging to the lead on the fence turning for home, stopped inside at the furlong marker, checked on the fence nearing the sixteenth pole and was not factor at the finish.
